edit: 12-28-2018
So I have been using this for a bit, and I have found a dislike, well at first it was a dislike. Then the ah hah moment came.

Wait for it......

It's the design of the charging cord. On the back of the unit, it plugs straight in and make the unit sit about an extra 1 1/2 - 2 inches from the wall. Why would you not put an "L" type plug on the unit for a more space saving design.
Wait for it.....
The plug causes the unit to sit just far enough from the wall so you can open the lid without having to adjust where its sitting. If you changed the plug it would require you to move the unit each time you used it. I would say well thought out design.

When I am out with friends and want to show them something on the internet, there is nothing worse than trying to show someone something on a tiny screen, but it isn't worth it to carry around a tablet just in case- for me anyway. The screen on this phone is beautiful and huge. This phone is great for showing people things on the internet or documents. Everyone that sees it agrees that it is a great screen, the biggest concern is the size of the device in its entirety.

This phone is comically huge. Most people (myself included) laugh at the sight of someone holding the phone to my ear. It looks and feels funny at first, but you get used to it and don't really think about it after a while. People are also concerned about the portability of this phone. I find that it fits in my work uniform pockets just fine. I also carry a purse, so carrying it is no issue. Men usually have larger pockets (unless they wear skinny jeans) and fitting the phone in there isn't an issue.

The stylus is almost a novelty except that it works great! This isn't based on the same technology that people use with their iPhone or other smart phones, so you will find that there is a great deal of accuracy! I find that it is almost unfair to use the stylus when playing Draw Something, but I still do.

While this phone doesn't have all the frequencies for 4G on t-mobile, it does have the download frequency. I am not sure if it is possible for the phone to get downloads at 4G speeds without the upload frequency, but I will say that my internet is faster than EDGE (which is what the phone says I am getting). I am able to stream videos with no problem and web pages load as quick as they ever did on my old 4G phone. The only thing that seems to take longer is sending e-mails, which would be consistent with my frequency hypothesis. I make no promises about performance, just telling you my experience.

The user interface is fine- and better than the US version. The battery lasts and lasts. Before I put lots of apps on the phone, the phone had no problem going a day and half an a single charge with regular use and hours of streaming music. The best battery I have seen on a phone!

text:
I like it but you should be aware that it may not be strong enough to hold your phone with the case on. I have an iPhone 7s with a leather case. In the packaging is a magnet which they tell you that you don't have to adhere to the phone. You can just put it between the case and the phone. So that's what I did. It worked well enough, but my phone kept leaning more and more one direction. Then more and more the other direction. It never survived too many bumps or turns before it was sideways and almost falling off. Also, if you charge your phone while on the mount, the drag of the cable is enough to make your phone move downward.

So, I removed my case and adhered the magnet to the back of my phone. Left the case off. Haven't had a problem since. Phone stays in place, even with charge cable and rough roads. This may not be convenient for everybody, but my case is easy to put on and take off, so I just slip it back on when I leave the car.

***UPDATE***
I'm reducing a star. I've stopped using this completely because it has a fundamental flaw. The bracket that goes into the CD slot is fine. But the round rubber covering around the magnets is what causes the phones to tilt left and right. After taking this apart, I see there is nothing that prevents the cover from rotating... not notches, no nothing. So the magnets hold nice and tight, but the rubber cover over the magnets looses its grip and rotates badly after a while. I've purchased a rectangular mount now and that should work fine for me.

I can't recommend anybody purchase this mount until they find a way to prevent the round rubber cover from moving on its own.

text:

text: [[VIDEOID:da0958ca0c019309d7380ec0c42e8d92]] It's often challenging to find a pretty case that offers sufficient protection for my large-screen phone. I am afraid this Kit Me out World sparkly gel case does not offer the level of protection I desire for my expensive XS max iPhone. This case is constructed with three layers that amount to nothing more than a sparkly piece of paper with a hard plastic backing and a flexible outer shell. None of the layers are aligned, and there are visible gaps, so it just looks cheap and poorly made. Perhaps I received a factory second because I have other cases by this manufacturer and the overall quality was much better. I thought I would love this case because it matches the color of my phone, but. I cannot recommend it based on the one I received.

title: Charges phone with thick Otterbox case, but doesn't hold it securely
text:
The UPSTONE Wireless Car Charger-Cup Phone Holder Mount is a fantastic idea and comes with several mounting adapters for air vents or dashboard mount. My thick Super Beetle case has defeated many chargers, but not this one. So where did this innovative charger pass or fall?

PASS

Charged my phone with an ultra thick case

Holds and charges phone with a more regular or average sized case

Multiple attachments to mount in an air vent or hard surface.

The automatic grip is very responsive

FAIL:

Even though it charges the phone with a thick Otterbox type case, but doesn't hold it securely. If I were to brake hard or hit a bump my phone drops out of the holder. It didn't take much jostling to drop the phone.
The side grips just aren't long enough or strong enough.

The automatic grip may be a little too touchy and responsive. It opened every time I touched anything near the phone.

I love the idea of a cup holder mount so I can place my phone in the most convenient and accessible location without blocking my AC vents. It also keeps the power cord away from my radio and AC controls located above my Cig Lighter adapter and I can plug into my console's auxiliary power more easily from the cup holder. I wish the cup holder mount was weighted a bit better. Overall I think it's a brilliant idea and I will do more real-world tests and update accordingly.

title: Worth every penny! Amazing breadth of features
text:
[[VIDEOID:95fd339a83b69625e3c3b0c38831fcb8]] My iPhone is the true test of any QI wireless charging device and has defeated 65% of the chargers I have tested and reviewed because of its thick "Otterbox" type case. So, how well did this Mangotek 4 in 1 Wireless Charger perform?

PHONE CHARGER:

Charged like a champ and had no issues with a super thick case. The positioning was a little finicky at first, but once I found the sweet spot, it worked flawlessly. iPhones do not support QC (quick charge) and are always much slower to charge when using QI wireless charging, so it charged about as fast as any of my other QI chargers. I have them everywhere, and my phone battery NEVER runs down because it is always docked in a QI charger when not in use.

APPLE WATCH CHARGER:

The charger is built into the unit, and it works! Rarely have I found a non-OEM watch charger that works with my Apple watch. There are no separate cords, and it can accommodate a 44mm watch with ease. The watch stand is attached with a knurled nut so you can remove it for traveling.

LIGHTNING CONNECTION:
There is an adjustable lightning connection to charge additional phones, ear pods, or any device that does not support QI wireless charging. I believe it will also accommodate an iPad.

OVERVIEW:
You would be hard pressed to find a more versatile and powerful charger. The Mangotek 4 in 1 Wireless Charger is a top-notch unit, and it comes with three types of adapters for several countries. The watch stand is detachable so it can be packed flat for travel. Are there cheaper QI units? Yes, but so far I haven't found one that works as well or has more built-in charging options than this one. The only other charger that worked with my phone was the Belkin, and it is at the same price point, but lacked the same amount of features. I would rate this unit 10 stars if I could. It is an excellent charger, and I highly recommend it.

text:

If you have a newer phone that supports wireless charging I think you may be happier the Belkin Qi charger. If you have a mix of old and new technology, as I do, you cannot go wrong with this one.

It's a weird set up and doesn't really support the watch as your would expect from the design of the case.

It's highly adjustable and just about any surface with an edge will do.
